          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "SNYK-UBUNTU2404-BINUTILS-13570212",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - Out-of-Bounds vulnerability in binutils"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2025-11495) binutils/binutils-common@2.42-4ubuntu2.10"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## NVD Description\n**_Note:_** _Versions mentioned in the description apply only to the upstream `binutils` package and not the `binutils` package as distributed by `Ubuntu`._\n_See `How to fix?` for `Ubuntu:24.04` relevant fixed versions and status._\n\nA vulnerability was determined in GNU Binutils 2.45. The affected element is the function elf_x86_64_relocate_section of the file elf64-x86-64.c of the component Linker. This manipulation causes heap-based buffer overflow. The attack can only be executed locally. The exploit has been publicly disclosed and may be utilized. Patch name: 6b21c8b2ecfef5c95142cbc2c32f185cb1c26ab0. To fix this issue, it is recommended to deploy a patch.\n## Remediation\nThere is no fixed version for `Ubuntu:24.04` `binutils`.\n## References\n- [http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-11495](http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-11495)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/attachment.cgi?id=16393](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/attachment.cgi?id=16393)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33502](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33502)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33502#c3](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33502#c3)\n- [https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=6b21c8b2ecfef5c95142cbc2c32f185cb1c26ab0](https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=6b21c8b2ecfef5c95142cbc2c32f185cb1c26ab0)\n- [https://vuldb.com/?ctiid.327620](https://vuldb.com/?ctiid.327620)\n- [https://vuldb.com/?id.327620](https://vuldb.com/?id.327620)\n- [https://vuldb.com/?submit.668290](https://vuldb.com/?submit.668290)\n- [https://www.gnu.org/](https://www.gnu.org/)\n- [https://cert-portal.siemens.com/productcert/html/ssa-082556.html](https://cert-portal.siemens.com/productcert/html/ssa-082556.html)\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-119",
                  "CWE-122",
                  "deb"
                ],
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.5,
                "security-severity": "5.5"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "SNYK-UBUNTU2404-BINUTILS-15440796",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - CVE-2025-69646 vulnerability in binutils"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2025-69646) binutils/binutils-common@2.42-4ubuntu2.10"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## NVD Description\n**_Note:_** _Versions mentioned in the description apply only to the upstream `binutils` package and not the `binutils` package as distributed by `Ubuntu`._\n_See `How to fix?` for `Ubuntu:24.04` relevant fixed versions and status._\n\nBinutils objdump contains a denial-of-service vulnerability when processing a crafted binary with malformed DWARF debug_rnglists data. A logic error in the handling of the debug_rnglists header can cause objdump to repeatedly print the same warning message and fail to terminate, resulting in an unbounded logging loop until the process is interrupted. The issue was observed in binutils 2.44. A local attacker can exploit this vulnerability by supplying a malicious input file, leading to excessive CPU and I/O usage and preventing completion of the objdump analysis.\n## Remediation\nThere is no fixed version for `Ubuntu:24.04` `binutils`.\n## References\n- [http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-69646](http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-69646)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33638](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33638)\n- [https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=598704a00cbac5e85c2bedd363357b5bf6fcee33](https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=598704a00cbac5e85c2bedd363357b5bf6fcee33)\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "deb"
                ],
                "cvssv3_baseScore": null,
                "security-severity": "null"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "SNYK-UBUNTU2404-BINUTILS-15440858",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - CVE-2025-69645 vulnerability in binutils"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2025-69645) binutils/binutils-common@2.42-4ubuntu2.10"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## NVD Description\n**_Note:_** _Versions mentioned in the description apply only to the upstream `binutils` package and not the `binutils` package as distributed by `Ubuntu`._\n_See `How to fix?` for `Ubuntu:24.04` relevant fixed versions and status._\n\nBinutils objdump contains a denial-of-service vulnerability when processing a crafted binary with malformed DWARF debug information. A logic error in the handling of DWARF compilation units can result in an invalid offset_size value being used inside byte_get_little_endian, leading to an abort (SIGABRT). The issue was observed in binutils 2.44. A local attacker can trigger the crash by supplying a malicious input file.\n## Remediation\nThere is no fixed version for `Ubuntu:24.04` `binutils`.\n## References\n- [http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-69645](http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-69645)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33637](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33637)\n- [https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=cdb728d4da6184631989b192f1022c219dea7677](https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=cdb728d4da6184631989b192f1022c219dea7677)\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "deb"
                ],
                "cvssv3_baseScore": null,
                "security-severity": "null"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "SNYK-UBUNTU2404-BINUTILS-15440868",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Medium severity - CVE-2025-69651 vulnerability in binutils"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "(CVE-2025-69651) binutils/binutils-common@2.42-4ubuntu2.10"
              },
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## NVD Description\n**_Note:_** _Versions mentioned in the description apply only to the upstream `binutils` package and not the `binutils` package as distributed by `Ubuntu`._\n_See `How to fix?` for `Ubuntu:24.04` relevant fixed versions and status._\n\nGNU Binutils thru 2.46 readelf contains a vulnerability that leads to an invalid pointer free when processing a crafted ELF binary with malformed relocation or symbol data. If dump_relocations returns early due to parsing errors, the internal all_relocations array may remain partially uninitialized. Later, process_got_section_contents() may attempt to free an invalid r_symbol pointer, triggering memory corruption checks in glibc and causing the program to terminate with SIGABRT. No evidence of further memory corruption or code execution was observed; the impact is limited to denial of service. NOTE: this is disputed by third parties because the observed behavior occurred only in pre-release code and did not affect any tagged version.\n## Remediation\nThere is no fixed version for `Ubuntu:24.04` `binutils`.\n## References\n- [http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-69651](http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2025-69651)\n- [https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=ea4bc025abdba85a90e26e13f551c16a44bfa921](https://sourceware.org/git/gitweb.cgi?p=binutils-gdb.git;h=ea4bc025abdba85a90e26e13f551c16a44bfa921)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33698](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33698)\n- [https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33700](https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33700)\n- [https://sourceware.org/git/?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=commitdiff;h=81e90cf63a10ad11772c2437c8f2a88f1a00c739](https://sourceware.org/git/?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=commitdiff;h=81e90cf63a10ad11772c2437c8f2a88f1a00c739)\n- [https://sourceware.org/git/?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=commitdiff;h=ea4bc025abdba85a90e26e13f551c16a44bfa92](https://sourceware.org/git/?p=binutils-gdb.git;a=commitdiff;h=ea4bc025abdba85a90e26e13f551c16a44bfa92)\n"
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "deb"
                ],
                "cvssv3_baseScore": 5.5,
                "security-severity": "5.5"
              }
